
= organizer and participant in the conference: [[Re-Thinking Property for a Well-Being Society]]


=Bio=

"Asst. Prof. Surat Horachaikul is a lecturer in the Department of International Relations, Faculty of Political Science, Chulalongkorn University and Director of the School for Wellbeing Studies and Research. He has master degrees from the London School of Economics and Political Science and from London Guildhall University. His recent publications include: “Democratic Development in Thailand”, Johnson’s Great Society: The Lesson for Thailand’s Poverty Alleviation” and “The Far South of Thailand in the Era of the American Empire, 9/11 Version."


